  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&apos;s goal is to contribute to reducing the suffering of the IDPs by meeting their survival needs in evacuation centers and with host families; and rebuilding their shelter, and recovering their livelihoods when they return home in Marawi city. There are two outcomes: 1) IDPs have sufficient access to a range of food and other needs for survival and dignity while displaced, and 2) IDPs have increased capacity to go back to their normal living conditions and livelihood activities in their original place.</narrative>
  </description>
